						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1470, Kīlaka, Vaiśākha, ba • • • Ādivāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1548 April 29</hi> or <hi rend="bold">May 6, Sunday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśiva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇapa-Nāyaka</hi> made a gift of the village <hi rend="bold">Nagarehaḷi,</hi> surnamed <hi rend="bold">Nagarūru,</hi> situated in <hi rend="bold">[Kuṇṭe]nūra-sīme</hi> in the <hi rend="bold">Kōgaḷi-vaḷita</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Timapa</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Bommapura.</hi> The record is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
